Data Science and Environmental Analytics, focusing on urban climate/environment/sustainability, aerosol and air quality, and environmental data science

"I am extremely interested in contributing to Turing’s Environment & Sustainability Grand Challenge.
For instance, my research aligns precisely with the missions.
(1) deliver localised environmental predictions to mitigate the impacts of climate change
and (2) Model interventions to achieve sustainable cities and regions for a net zero world"
notes.335: TWINE Digital Twin Ocean demonstrator has been approved. TRIC-DT provided LOS.
notes.500: Coffee chat with Harry Meacher: I thought perhaps the community element of our grand challenge could possibly engage with the community FP has cultivated. Whilst it seems predominantly industry, there could be scope to build networks off the back of this.
notes.515: work closely with Sara Bernardini on the E&S Grand Challenge. Prior to NOC, I worked at Microsoft as Europe Lead for Sustainability Science and the Met Office where I had various roles, including leading the Informatics department and the near-term climate prediction section. I have also been a Turing Fellow in the past.
